<h2 class="Title">2023 single-family residential water rates</h2>
<p>The Las Vegas Valley Water District (LVVWD) has made significant changes to residential water rates to further support water conservation amid the ongoing drought and federally imposed water reductions from Lake Mead. The changes include an excessive use charge, as well as a tier equalization change that uses the same tier thresholds for all residential customers.&#160;<a href="customer-service/pay-bill/water-rates.html">Review the 2023 water rates</a> and <a href="customer-service/pay-bill/water-bill-estimator/index.cfml">estimate your water bill.</a></p>
<h3 style="font-size: 120%;">Trouble paying?</h3>
<p>If you are experiencing financial hardship and are having trouble paying your bill, you may qualify for assistance from&#160;the <a href="https://dwss.nv.gov/Energy/Apply_for_Water_and_Sewer_Assistance/">State of Nevada</a>. <a href="customer-service/pay-bill/index.html#assistance">Learn more</a>.</p>
                    				                        				                    				
                    				                    				
